    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This project focuses on analyzing restaurant data from Zomato using machine learning techniques to uncover meaningful patterns and insights about the restaurant industry. Zomato is a widely used restaurant discovery and food delivery platform that provides detailed information about restaurants, including cuisine types, price ranges, ratings, and customer reviews. The primary vision of this project is to use **data analytics** and **machine learning methods** to extract meaningful insights from this data in order to better understand restaurant characteristics, customer preferences, and emerging market trends within the food industry.\n",
        "\n",
        "A major component of the project is the use of **unsupervised machine learning techniques** to group restaurants into meaningful segments. Clustering algorithms such as **K-Means and Hierarchical Clustering** will be applied to group restaurants based on features such as cuisine type, price range, ratings, and customer engagement metrics. These clusters help reveal hidden structures within the dataset by identifying restaurants that share similar characteristics. In order to determine the most appropriate number of clusters, evaluation methods such as the **Elbow Methods, Dendograms and Silhouette Score** will be used. These techniques help measure cluster quality and ensure that the grouping process produces meaningful and interpretable results.\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset used in this project contains two major categories of information: restaurant details and customer review data. The restaurant dataset includes attributes such as restaurant names, cost per person, cuisine categories, and collection tags assigned by the Zomato platform. The review dataset contains reviewer information, textual reviews, ratings, timestamps, number of images posted, and metadata such as follower counts and total reviews written by users.\n",
        "\n",
        "The project begins with **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** to examine the structure and distribution of the dataset. Visualization techniques such as bar charts, histograms, and correlation analysis will be used to identify patterns such as the popularity of different cuisines, the distribution of restaurant pricing, and the relationship between cost and customer ratings. These insights help guide feature selection and prepare the dataset for machine learning tasks.\n",
        "\n",
        "After exploratory analysis, the next phase includes ** Feature Engineering and Pre-Processing**, the dataset undergoes **data cleaning and preprocessing**, which includes handling missing values, removing or treating outliers, and converting categorical variables into numerical representations through encoding techniques. In addition, numerical features are standardized using scaling methods such as **Standard Scaler or Min-Max Scaler** to ensure that all variables contribute equally to the clustering process.\n",
        "\n",
        "Another important aspect of the project is the use of **sentiment analysis on customer reviews** through natural language processing techniques. By analyzing the text of reviews, sentiment scores can be generated to classify feedback as positive, neutral, or negative. This allows the project to compare textual sentiment with numerical ratings and identify deeper insights about customer satisfaction and dining experiences.\n",
        "\n",
        "In addition to clustering and sentiment analysis, the project also introduces a **restaurant recommendation system**. By calculating similarity between restaurant feature vectors, the system can recommend restaurants that share similar characteristics such as cuisine type, price range, and rating. This demonstrates how machine learning insights can be applied to build practical recommendation tools that help users discover new restaurants aligned with their preferences.\n",
        "\n",
        "To further enhance the analysis, the project develops a **Restaurant Success Score**, a custom scoring algorithm that combines multiple indicators such as ratings, number of reviews, sentiment scores, and customer engagement metrics. This composite score helps rank restaurants more comprehensively rather than relying on a single metric.\n",
        "\n",
        "The project will be implemented using Python libraries such as **Pandas and NumPy for data manipulation, Matplotlib and Seaborn for visualization, and Scikit-learn for machine learning algorithms and clustering analysis**.\n",
        "\n",
        "Overall, the project demonstrates how machine learning, data analysis, and natural language processing techniques can be applied to real-world restaurant data to generate meaningful insights and support data-driven decision making within the food service industry."
